SIMPLE: dehiscence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dehiscence
<hw>De*his"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧hiscence</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
gaping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A gaping or bursting open along a
definite line of attachment or suture, without tearing, as in the
opening of pods, or the bursting of capsules at maturity so as to emit
seeds, etc.; also, the bursting open of follicles, as in the ovaries of
animals, for the expulsion of their contents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dehiscent</ent>⟦br⟧
